article.headline: Jones scores last 2 points, finishes with 29 in Weber State's 70-69 victory against Idaho
article.description: — Dillon Jones scored the last two points and finished with 29 points in Weber State's 70-69 win over Idaho on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Jones scores last 2 points, finishes with 29 in Weber State's 70-69 victory against Idaho
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- — Dillon Jones scored the last two points and finished with 29 points in Weber State's 70-69 win over Idaho on Thursday night. Jones made a pair of free throws with seven seconds left. Quinn Denker missed a 3-pointer to end it. Jones had six rebounds and nine assists for the Wildcats (17-9, 8-5 Big Sky Conference). Dyson Koehler scored 11 points and added three steals. Julius Mims led the Vandals (9-16, 3-9) in scoring, finishing with 17 points, eight rebounds and two blocks. Denker scored 13 points and had seven assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
